{
  "description": "Crossover fixtures for the Irene<->bridge canonical-command contract: {utterance -> expected canonical command}. Producer half: Irene's TEST-18 suite asserts the captured command equals `expect`. Consumer half: the bridge's VWB-16 replays `expect` against its native layer. Authored by wb-mqtt-voice (TEST-18 Slice A); bound to the pinned catalog below — re-author bindings on re-pin if the guard test fails.",
  "catalog_version": "5622ba7a1a78102a",
  "expect_kinds": {
    "actuate": "device-form command: POST /devices/{device_id}/canonical {capability, action, params}",
    "room-group": "room-form command (VWB-23): POST /rooms/{room_id}/canonical {group, action, scope}; scope auto = bare noun, all = the plural/«весь» signal",
    "read": "state read (ARCH-8 PR-5): GET /devices/{device_id}/state -> capability.field; `any_of` lists equally-correct targets",
    "clarify": "no command emitted: Irene asks a clarification naming the candidate devices; `capability` (string or list) = every candidate carries at least one of these, proving the ambiguity is genuine (a list since DRV-28: the same user goal can bind different capabilities per device — set-temperature is climate.set_setpoint on a floor, temperature.set on an AC)"
  },
  "tiers": {
    "1": "green-able with the current baseline: T1 donations + transliteration-tolerant matching (QUAL-35 Slice 1: «ютуб»↔YouTube, «эппл ти ви»↔Apple TV) + compound numerals (BUG-23/24 fixed the corrupting stages)",
    "2": "the QUAL-35 Slice 3 residue (2026-07-06): F90-F93/F95 are colloquial-lexicon fixtures GREEN only with the QUAL-50 LLM NLU tier in the cascade (enabled in RU deployment configs; run `make device-auto TIER=2 NLU=llm`) — deliberately NOT added to the T1 donations (the smart-home guide documents that recipe instead); F100-F102 are relative adjustments «поярче»/«потеплее» whose read-modify-write build is DEFERRED past first release. F94/F96/F97/F98 graduated to tier 1 (utterance scan / donation pattern fixes)"
  },
  "excluded_by_design": [
    "anaphora («сделай его поярче») — no last-addressed-device memory exists in conversation context; new context machinery, later release",
    "multi-command sentences («яркость 30 и температуру 22») and negation («весь свет кроме торшера») — the pipeline is one-Intent-per-utterance end to end; breaking that is its own design task, later release",
    "source→destination roles («со спальни на кухню») — no capability in the catalog moves anything between rooms; not actionable",
    "free-text spans («напомни выключить плиту») — timer/reminder domain, no bridge command; out of this suite's scope",
    "Cyrillic-spoken Latin names («ютуб», «эппл ти ви») — transliteration-tolerant matching is QUAL-35 T2; F41/F53 encode it and stay red until then",
    "light-subset pair nouns («ночники»/«тумбочки»/«полки») — dropped from v1; return as fixtures when the bridge adds compound devices for the pairs (needs a re-pin)",
    "power-group fan-out («выключи все розетки» as a room-group) — the bridge allow-lists fan-out to light+cover only; plugs/oven are reachable by NAME (see F04/F03), never by «свет»",
    "priority rules for same-room ambiguity — v1 clarifies (F20/F21); priorities are a later-release enhancement"
  ],
